description:
&lt;p&gt;‘Together We Care’&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an opportunity to work with an employer that cares about you? Would you like to work in a hospital with an international reputation for innovation? Do excellent public transport links and a range of local amenities appeal to you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the answer to these questions is YES, then take a look at the Sheffield Children’s Hospital for your next career destination. Rated good in a 2019 CQC inspection, we strive to deliver excellent care to our patients in a friendly and compassionate environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an NHS employer we can offer you a first rate package including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attractive pension (with employer contributions and tax relief)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous annual leave allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice schemes (e.g. cycle to work)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounts with high street and online retailers (through our partnership with Vivup)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to other discount services (e.g. Blue Light Card)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we expect you to demonstrate Excellence, Accountability, Compassion, Teamwork and Integrity. If you’re up for the challenge, then read on to see whether you have the right skills for the job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;­­­­­­­__________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sheffield Children’s Hospital are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated individual to recruit to a part time, Secretarial Assistant vacancy (22.5 hrs) within the NeuroDisability Assessment Team in the Division of Medicine. Please note this post is based at our Ryegate Children&#39;s Centre, Tapton Crescent Road, Sheffield S10 5DD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant must possess excellent organisational and interpersonal skills. They will be flexible and conscientious with the ability to liaise with staff of all levels throughout the hospital and to the wider Trust, as well as parents/guardians and GPs dealing effectively and efficiently with telephone enquiries. This post primarily requires the successful candidate to produce dictated correspondence using both audio and digital transcribers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to provide quality administrative and secretarial support services to the Secretarial team working efficiently with current systems and processes and ensuring security and accessibility of relevant information and documentation to help underpin the smooth running of the office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work under the direction of the Team Leader, but will be capable of using your own initiative. They will be required to adopt a flexible approach and must enjoy working as part of a mixed skilled team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure that you explain clearly how you meet the essential and desirable criteria in your application.&lt;/p&gt;
